#EXDESC
ExDescKey    chalk board chalkboard~
ExDesc       Once you are in space, you can move around. Moving may seem complicated at
first, but it really isn't. It is done by directing your suit towards 3
coordinates, <x>, <y>, and <z>. So if you type "course 100 100 100", it
would bring you towards those coordinates. To see if there is anything
worthwhile going to, type radar, and it will show you anything else in the
starsystem. To control the speed at which you're going, type "speed
<speed>", <speed> being the number you'd wish to go at. If you type "speed
0", it will bring your suit to a complete stop. Typing Status will show
you your current coordinates, as well as the coordinates  you're heading.
Pay special attention to your fuel, if it goes down to 0, you blow up!
~
#ENDEXDESC

